\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 WordPress is a great tool for beginners especially for creating posts, pages, menus, and users. However, things are not welcoming for the developers as they often need to create dummy data while creating websites.\
Good news for you if you also have a similar intention, as you can effortlessly create pages, posts, menus, and users programmatically.\'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Key Takeaways\'a0
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 \
In this blog post, I will walk you through the following things:\
\uc0\u10004  Prerequisites for Creating Things Programmatically\
\uc0\u10004  Create Custom Page Programmatically in WordPress\
\uc0\u10004  Create Posts Programmatically in WordPress\
\uc0\u10004  Create Menu Programmatically in WordPress\
\uc0\u10004  Create a User Programmatically in WordPress\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa398\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs48 \cf2 \cb3 Why Create Pages, Posts, Menus, and User Programmatically? (Real-World Use Cases)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 At first glance, it may seem unnecessary to create pages, posts, menus, or users through code was WordPress has a simplified UI to do this. However, in real-world development scenarios, a programmatic approach is not only useful but also essential. Let\'92s explore why:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 Rapidly Set Up New Websites\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 WordPress developers often need to create new websites. So, they need to use dummy content as the site owners can easily add or update their content after completing the development. So, with the programmatic approach, they can easily create essential pages like About, Contact, Privacy Policy, etc.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 Staging / Testing Environment\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Not just dummy content, the developers may also need images, custom pages, news users, etc, for testing themes or plugins. With the coding approach, they can instantly accomplish their goal and create testing environments.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 Client Projects\'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 The freelance developers must add some dummy content while delivering their project, otherwise the sites will not look good. And the coding approaches help them to do it with ease.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 Add New User / Login Access\'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 The developers can also create user roles by adding a few lines of code to their theme\'92s functions.php file. This method is also useful if you have lost login access and had issues while resetting your password.\'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa398\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs48 \cf2 \cb3 Prerequisites: What You Need Before Starting\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Before you start playing with code, there are some essential things that need to be ensured. Setting up the following things will not only help you accomplish your goal, but you can avoid unwanted situations.\'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 Backup Your Website\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 I shouldn\'92t tell you this if you have been writing codes for some time, as you must have a backup of your site. I still remember my early days when I used to do experiments with codes to tweak my WordPress site. I faced a lot of errors, thanks to the support team of Namecheap for helping me restore backups of my site.\'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 Use a Child Theme\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Another must-have thing is a child theme before starting to add custom codes. Without having a child theme, your changes in the theme\'92s code are removed with the latest updates. So, to avoid this kind of situation, you must install a child theme on your website.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 Basic Knowledge of WordPress and PHP\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 If you really want to add custom codes to your site, you must have a basic knowledge of coding especially PHP as we are going to use it to accomplish the goal. Yes, I know that being a coder is not necessary in this generation of AI. However, you should at least have knowledge about how coding actually works.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 Have Access to Theme Files\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 It is not mandatory to be the website owner to create posts, pages, etc programmatically. You can also do it on behalf of the site owner. However, you must have access to the theme files.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 Enable Debugging in WordPress\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Last but not least, you should enable the WordPress debugging mode. So that you can find out the error in case something goes wrong. Don\'92t worry if you are not familiar with this as we have a detailed guide on enabling {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.wpxpo.com/how-to-enable-error-reporting-in-wordpress/"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 \cb3 \ul \ulc2 WordPress error reporting}}.\'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa398\partightenfactor0

