\f2\b\fs48 \cf2 \cb3 Troubleshooting: Common Errors and How to Fix Them\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 No matter if you write the codes yourself or collect them from other sources, you may face some uses here and there. So I have tried to collect the most common problems and fixes to help you out.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 Error: \'93Page/Post Not Appearing on the Frontend\'94\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Cause:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3  You may face a post status issue while creating custom posts or pages.\

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Solution:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3  To avoid this, you must ensure that the parameter of the post_status is set to publish. If not, WordPress will create the posts/pages as drafts.\'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 Error: \'93Menu Items Not Displaying\'94\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Cause: 
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 The custom menu creation process will not work if it is not correctly assigned to the location.\

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Solution:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3  So make sure to assign the menu properly to your preferred location using the wp_nav_menu function.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 Error: \'93Incorrect Post Type or Page Template\'94\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Cause:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3  My current code will not work if you have custom templates without modifying the name of the template.\

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Solution:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3  So if you are using a custom template on your site, make use of adding the name of that in the page_template parameter.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 Error: \'93Missing Content or Fields\'94\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Cause:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3  If the codes are not written properly, some fields like title, content, or metadata will not be visible.\

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Solution:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3  So make sure to pass all of your required post elements using the wp_insert_post() or wp_create_nav_menu() calls.\
